This paper deals with the problem of predicting future attack sources based on logs and alerts contributed by multiple organizations. This problem falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also involves the measurement and analysis of state-of-the-art CPB techniques, which involves data sharing and privacy-preserving approaches. This aspect of the paper could also fit under the categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), social and information networks (cs.SI), machine learning (cs.LG), and cryptography and security (cs.CY).
